Class Domain

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object>, java.util.Set<java.lang.Object>

    public class Domain
extends ArraySet<java.lang.Object>
    A Domain represents an ordered set of possible Values for a Variable. Technically of course a set needn't be ordered, but it might make life easier to use a List here...

    We use a ArraySet here since iteration is the main use for Domains in Bayes nets algorithms.
